StreamLens — Production-Grade ML Search & Recommendation Platform
Built by Akila Lourdes Miriyala Francis · MS in Artificial Intelligence
GitHub: https://github.com/AKilalours/streaming-canvas-search-ltr
LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/akila-lourdes-miriyala-francis-5b047019a/

This project was built entirely from scratch as an independent portfolio project
demonstrating production-grade ML engineering across:
- Learning-to-Rank (LightGBM LambdaRank, nDCG@10 = 0.9300)
- Dense retrieval (fine-tuned intfloat/e5-base-v2, +18.4% improvement)
- GenAI explanation layer (GPT-4o-mini, 44 languages)
- MLOps pipeline (Airflow, Metaflow, 14 flows, 9 quality gates)
- Real-time serving (FastAPI, Redis, Kafka, WebSocket)
- Causal inference (Doubly-Robust IPW, Off-Policy Evaluation)

Third-party datasets and models used under their respective licenses:
- MovieLens dataset: © GroupLens Research, University of Minnesota
  License: https://grouplens.org/datasets/movielens/
- intfloat/e5-base-v2: MIT License
- LightGBM: MIT License
- CLIP ViT-B/32: MIT License (OpenAI)
- OpenAI API: Subject to OpenAI Terms of Service
- TMDB API: Subject to TMDB Terms of Use
